			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote8-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote8-02291_002_019">8.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.110?lang=spa#109" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 88:110</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.64?lang=spa#63" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 7:64</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote9-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote10-02291_002_019">10.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase Bruce R. McConkie, &ldquo;La caravana contin&uacute;a su marcha&rdquo;, <span class="emphasis">Liahona</span>, enero de 1985, p&aacute;gs. 68&ndash;70.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote10-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote11-02291_002_019">11.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/dan/2.44-45?lang=spa#43" target="_blank">Daniel 2:44–45</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/38.9-15?lang=spa#8" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 38:9–15</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.24?lang=spa#23" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 82:24</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote11-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote12-02291_002_019">12.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.17-19?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">José Smith—Historia 1:17–19</a> (la aparici&oacute;n del Padre y del Hijo a Jos&eacute; Smith fue la primera vez que eso ocurr&iacute;a desde el Jard&iacute;n de Ed&eacute;n); <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.30-49?lang=spa#29" target="_blank">José Smith—Historia 1:30–49</a> (Moroni); <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/27.7-8,12-13?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 27:7–8, 12–13</a> (Juan el Bautista, Pedro, Santiago y Juan); <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/110.11-16?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 110:11–16</a> (Mois&eacute;s, El&iacute;as y El&iacute;as el profeta); <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.19-21?lang=spa#18" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 128:19–21</a> (&ldquo;diversos &aacute;ngeles, desde Miguel o Ad&aacute;n, hasta el tiempo actual&rdquo;).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote12-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote12-02291_002_019">12.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/13.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Alma 13:3</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote13-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote13-02291_002_019">13.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/101.55?lang=spa#54" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 101:55</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/105.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 105:16</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote14-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote14-02291_002_019">14.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rev/12.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">Apocalipsis 12:12</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote15-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote15-02291_002_019">15.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 27:13</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote16-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote16-02291_002_019">16.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rev/12.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Apocalipsis 12:17</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote17-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote17-02291_002_019">17.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/2-tim/3.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">2 Timoteo 3:1</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote18-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote18-02291_002_019">18.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Boyd K. Packer, &ldquo;La &uacute;nica defensa pura&rdquo; (discurso pronunciado ante educadores religiosos del SEI, 6 de febrero de 2004), p&aacute;g. 4.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote19-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote19-02291_002_019">19.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Alma aconsej&oacute; a cada uno de sus hijos &mdash;Helam&aacute;n, Shibl&oacute;n y Coriant&oacute;n&mdash; que fueran &ldquo;[juiciosos]&rdquo; (v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.47?lang=spa#46" target="_blank">Alma 37:47</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Alma 38:15</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/42.31?lang=spa#30" target="_blank">Alma 42:31</a>). Pablo tambi&eacute;n exhort&oacute; a los hombres j&oacute;venes a ser &ldquo;prudentes&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/titus/2.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Tito 2:6</a>). Adem&aacute;s, Pablo aconsej&oacute; a otros que fueran sobrios, en especial a los obispos (v&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/12.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Romanos 12:3</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-thes/5.6,8?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">1 Tesalonicenses 5:6, 8</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-tim/3.2,11?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">1 Timoteo 3:2, 11</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/titus/1.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Tito 1:8</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/titus/2.2,4,12?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Tito 2:2, 4, 12</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote20-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote20-02291_002_019">20.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/53.20-21?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">Alma 53:20&ndash;21</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote21-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote21-02291_002_019">21.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Morm&oacute;n 1:2</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote22-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote22-02291_002_019">22.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Morm&oacute;n 1:15</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote23-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote23-02291_002_019">23.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase Gordon B. Hinckley, &ldquo;Un conflicto interminable, una victoria asegurada&rdquo;, <span class="emphasis">Liahona</span>, junio de 2007, p&aacute;gs. 2&ndash;7.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote24-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-02291_002_019">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://scriptures.byu.edu/getscrip.php?ID=117389">TJS, Apocalipsis 12:9, 11</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote25-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-02291_002_019">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.53?lang=spa#52" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 76:53</a> (los que heredan el reino celestial &ldquo;vencen por la fe&rdquo;); <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-jn/5.4-5?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">1 Juan 5:4&ndash;5</a> (&ldquo;esta es la victoria que ha vencido al mundo, nuestra fe&rdquo;, y &ldquo;el que vence al mundo&rdquo; es &ldquo;el que cree que Jes&uacute;s es el Hijo de Dios&rdquo;.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote26-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-02291_002_019">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.11-15?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">José Smith—Historia 1:11–15</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote27-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-02291_002_019">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/heb/11.1?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Hebreos 11:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.21?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">Alma 32:21</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">&Eacute;ter 12:6</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote28-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-02291_002_019">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">La voz del Se&ntilde;or se describe como una voz apacible de perfecta suavidad, como si fuera un susurro. V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/19.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">1 Reyes 19:12</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/5.30?lang=spa#29" target="_blank">Helam&aacute;n 5:30</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/85.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 85:6</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote29-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-02291_002_019">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.69,121?lang=spa#68" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 88:69, 121</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote30-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-02291_002_019">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/16.24-25?lang=spa#23" target="_blank">Mateo 16:24&ndash;25</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/7.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Juan 7:17</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote31-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-02291_002_019">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/6.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">Efesios 6:16</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote32-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-02291_002_019">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-tim/6.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">1 Timoteo 6:12</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote33-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-02291_002_019">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/mal/3.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Malaqu&iacute;as 3:2</a>. &ldquo;&iquest;y qui&eacute;n podr&aacute; sostenerse en pie?&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rev/6.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Apocalipsis 6:17</a>). Aqu&eacute;llos que se han vestido con &ldquo;toda la armadura de Dios&rdquo; y han &ldquo;acabado todo&rdquo; (<a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/6.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">Efesios 6:13</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote34-02291_002_019"><a name="-02291_002_019">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-02291_002_019">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/ex/14.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">&Eacute;xodo 14:13</a>.</p>
			</li> </ol>
                                            
